1 (3) The grant recipient must have a project management plan that clearly outlines the roles of
2 participating entities and that is approved by the department of natural resources and conservation.
3 (4) The grant recipient shall comply with the auditing and reporting requirements provided for in 2-
4 7-503 and establish a financial accounting system that the department can reasonably ensure conforms to
5 generally accepted accounting principles. Tribal governments shall comply with the auditing and reporting
6 requirements provided for in 2 CFR 200.
7 (5) The grant recipient shall submit documentation to the department demonstrating satisfactory
8 completion of the conditions of described in the recommendation section of the project narrative of the program
9 report to the legislature for the biennium ending June 30, 2027, or, in the case of planning grants issued under
10 [section 1(1)], complete the conditions specified at the time of written notification of the approved grant
11 authority.
12 (6) The grant recipient shall execute a grant agreement with the department of natural resources
13 and conservation.
14 (7) Any other specific requirements considered necessary by the department must be met to
15 accomplish the purpose of the grant as evidenced from the application to the department or from the proposal
16 as presented to the legislature.
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Appropriations established. There is appropriated to any entity of state
19 government that receives a grant under [section 1] the amount of the grant upon award of the grant by the
20 department of natural resources and conservation. Grants to entities from prior biennia are reauthorized for the
21 completion of contract work.
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Approval of grants -- completion of biennial appropriation. The
24 legislature, pursuant to 90-2-1111, approves the reclamation and development grants listed in [section 1]. The
25 authorization of these grants constitutes a biennial appropriation from the natural resources projects state
26 special revenue account established in 15-38-302.
27
